<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="344" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/2541</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">10 May, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: After all, this<note n="*" xml:id="d344fn1">Page’s despatch about the <hi rend="italic">Lusitania</hi>, which I find I have burned. [Footnote in the
                                original. The despatch is printed in <ref target="frus1915Supp#pg_385">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1915, supp., p.
                                    385</ref>.]</note> does not express Page’s own opinion, but what
                            he takes to be public opinion at the moment in Great Britain.</p>
                        <p>It is a very serious thing to have such things thought, because
                            everything that affects the opinion of the world regarding us affects
                            our influence for good.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>